if you don't want to use these services
it easier to just use these "dummy" stubs for the services

That way when somebody requests the Event service for example they don't get a missing service error.

They could also the containers method "getServiceIfExists" which won't throw a error on a missing service
but instead simply return null. You could then test for this before calling a method on the server

in the __construct()
    
    $this->eventService = Container::getServiceIfExists('event');

In a method which needs to call a method on the service
    
    if ($this->eventService) {
        $this->eventService->trigger('load.model');
    }

using the stub as a service

in the __construct()
    
    $this->eventService = Container::getService('event');

In a method which needs to call a method on the service
    
    $this->eventService->trigger('load.model');
